WEBVTT

00:09.226 --> 00:09.400
.

00:09.444 --> 00:11.533
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:11.576 --> 00:13.143
sexually based offenses

00:13.187 --> 00:15.145
are considered
especially heinous.

00:15.189 --> 00:17.495
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:17.539 --> 00:19.323
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:19.367 --> 00:20.846
are members of an elite squad

00:20.890 --> 00:22.587
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:22.631 --> 00:24.415
These are their stories.

00:25.721 --> 00:28.680
- So are you ready to teach me
some of those dance moves?

00:28.724 --> 00:30.204
- Yeah.

00:30.247 --> 00:31.814
Can we get ice cream?
We're right by the cart.

00:31.857 --> 00:34.643
- Before dinner?
- I won't have dessert after.

00:36.210 --> 00:37.733
- Olivia!

00:41.215 --> 00:43.043
- Simon.

00:44.827 --> 00:47.134
- Hello, I'm Simon.

00:47.177 --> 00:48.570
- Hi, I'm Noah.

00:48.613 --> 00:51.225
- Yeah, go ahead.
Go pick a flavor, run along.

00:52.661 --> 00:54.402
- Who's Noah?

00:54.445 --> 00:56.665
- Uh, Noah is my son.

00:56.708 --> 00:58.710
- I have a nephew
and you didn't tell me?

00:58.754 --> 01:00.625
Well, that's on me.

01:00.669 --> 01:03.628
I haven't exactly
been in touch.

01:03.672 --> 01:06.109
- Simon,
what are you doing here?

01:06.153 --> 01:07.850
- I moved back
to Jersey a few years ago,

01:07.893 --> 01:09.547
working at the Carpet King.

01:09.591 --> 01:12.376
- How is your family,
your--your children?

01:12.420 --> 01:14.378
- I don't know.

01:14.422 --> 01:17.686
Tracy took the kids,
so I haven't seen her or them

01:17.729 --> 01:19.688
since I last saw you.

01:21.603 --> 01:23.387
- I'm sorry.

01:23.431 --> 01:25.607
- I thought about asking you
to help me track them down...

01:25.650 --> 01:29.393
but I always end up
making more trouble for you.

01:31.265 --> 01:32.570
Look, Olivia, I just...

01:32.614 --> 01:34.746
I just want
to make it up to you.

01:34.790 --> 01:37.401
Maybe I can--I can take
you and Noah out to lunch?

01:37.445 --> 01:39.142
- Simon, I don't think
that's such a good...

01:39.186 --> 01:40.578
- Just don't--don't say no.

01:40.622 --> 01:42.667
All right, look,
I've been clean five years.

01:42.711 --> 01:44.408
Look at this.

01:44.452 --> 01:48.238
All right?
You're my only family.

01:48.282 --> 01:50.371
I wanna get to know my nephew.

01:52.460 --> 01:55.463
Come on.
Wednesday, lunch.

01:55.506 --> 01:57.900
It's my day off.
You pick the place, the time.

01:57.943 --> 01:59.684
I can be anywhere.

01:59.728 --> 02:02.687
[somber music]

02:02.731 --> 02:07.779
♪

02:07.823 --> 02:10.695
- Eight Bronx Science grads
have won Nobel Prizes.

02:10.739 --> 02:12.436
I'm gonna be the ninth.

02:12.480 --> 02:14.786
- Good for you, Lupe.

02:14.830 --> 02:15.961
[upbeat pop music]

02:16.005 --> 02:17.528
- ♪ Me and my girls

02:17.572 --> 02:20.183
♪ We in charge,
call the shots ♪

02:20.227 --> 02:20.966
♪

02:21.010 --> 02:22.403
♪ Me and my girls

02:22.446 --> 02:24.231
- That's a lucky ice cream.

02:24.274 --> 02:26.320
- Dream on.

02:27.669 --> 02:30.367
- She's a herb,
but smart's hot, too.

02:30.411 --> 02:32.500
- ♪ Me and my girls

02:32.543 --> 02:35.590
♪ Live it up like we should

02:35.633 --> 02:37.809
♪ Me and my girls

02:37.853 --> 02:39.942
♪

02:39.985 --> 02:42.510
♪ Me and my girls

02:42.553 --> 02:44.816
♪

02:44.860 --> 02:47.515
[metal clanking]

02:47.558 --> 02:50.213
♪

02:50.257 --> 02:52.259
♪ Me and my girls

02:52.302 --> 02:54.478
♪

02:54.522 --> 02:57.220
[door closes]

02:57.264 --> 02:58.874
[ominous music]

02:58.917 --> 03:01.746
- [gasps]

03:01.790 --> 03:03.792
[muffled]
No!

03:03.835 --> 03:06.795
[whimpering]

03:06.838 --> 03:12.627
♪

03:12.670 --> 03:15.630
[dramatic music]

03:15.673 --> 03:22.680
♪

04:00.762 --> 04:02.894
[siren wailing]

04:02.938 --> 04:04.983
[indistinct chatter]

04:05.027 --> 04:07.334
- Well, the word is
definitely on the street.

04:07.377 --> 04:09.336
- Hey, move aside,
folks, please.

04:09.379 --> 04:11.686
Thank you.

04:11.729 --> 04:13.035
- Five-oh,
always five-oh minutes late.

04:13.078 --> 04:15.080
- No city cameras
to protect our girls,

04:15.124 --> 04:17.474
but plenty for mug shots
of our boys.

04:17.518 --> 04:20.390
- We're SVU, ma'am,
not the Warrant Squad.

04:20.434 --> 04:23.698
[dramatic music]

04:23.741 --> 04:26.396
♪

04:26.440 --> 04:29.051
- Lupe Perez, 14,
assaulted in the stairwell.

04:29.094 --> 04:31.053
She's still in shock,
but she didn't want to leave

04:31.096 --> 04:33.708
her little sister upstairs
alone, so I put a uni with her.

04:33.751 --> 04:35.666
- You got here fast.
- Two train.

04:35.710 --> 04:37.799
Faster than lights
and sirens every time.

04:37.842 --> 04:39.453
CSU is on the way.

04:39.496 --> 04:40.628
- And the girl's parents?

04:40.671 --> 04:41.846
- Her mom works the night shift

04:41.890 --> 04:44.022
at the Double Dutch
Donuts on 125th.

04:44.066 --> 04:45.763
- Cameras?

04:45.807 --> 04:48.766
- Busted, like the elevator.
Like always.

04:48.810 --> 04:51.552
- Wait a minute,
you're a former projects kid?

04:51.595 --> 04:52.814
- Gowanus.

04:52.857 --> 04:55.643
And no such thing
as a former projects kid.

04:55.686 --> 04:57.122
- Okay.

04:57.166 --> 04:59.429
Is the girl
comfortable with you?

04:59.473 --> 05:01.518
Why don't you ride
with her to CAC?

05:06.654 --> 05:09.613
- The doctor was nice,
but the exam hurt.

05:09.657 --> 05:11.441
- Lo siento.

05:11.485 --> 05:13.574
- Teenage girl
assaulted in the projects?

05:13.617 --> 05:15.053
Any witnesses?

05:15.097 --> 05:16.664
- Fin's still canvassing,
but there's nothing

05:16.707 --> 05:18.622
on the rape kit,
no semen or hairs.

05:18.666 --> 05:20.145
- So we're looking at a pro.

05:20.189 --> 05:21.973
- But we really want
to catch this guy.

05:22.017 --> 05:23.845
- You're letting
Kat take the lead?

05:23.888 --> 05:26.369
- We're giving her a shot.
She was first on scene,

05:26.413 --> 05:29.459
she rode with her,
and she took the disclosure...

05:29.503 --> 05:31.418
And I'm right here
if she needs me.

05:31.461 --> 05:33.115
- Kat doesn't miss a trick.

05:33.158 --> 05:35.378
Somebody must've stolen
her lunch money once.

05:35.422 --> 05:37.162
- Or tried to.

05:37.206 --> 05:39.077
- I tried
to scratch him for DNA,

05:39.121 --> 05:42.472
but he choked me
with my headphone cord.

05:42.516 --> 05:44.126
- Did you see his hands?

05:44.169 --> 05:47.521
- Big, white maybe.

05:47.564 --> 05:49.740
Or Hispanic.

05:49.784 --> 05:51.829
They smelled bad.

05:51.873 --> 05:53.831
- What kind of smells?

05:53.875 --> 05:56.399
- Like a woody smell.

05:56.443 --> 05:58.140
- Good, like, like a park?

05:58.183 --> 06:00.969
- No, pencil sharpener smell.

06:01.012 --> 06:03.885
- Good, Lupe.
Did you hear his voice?

06:06.017 --> 06:07.845
- He said...

06:07.889 --> 06:10.500
"Okay, chiquita,

06:10.544 --> 06:13.503
do it nice for Papi."

06:13.547 --> 06:16.550
[somber music]

06:16.593 --> 06:17.551
♪

06:17.594 --> 06:19.857
My real papi died.

06:19.901 --> 06:22.860
- I'm so sorry, Lupe.

06:22.904 --> 06:24.645
You okay?

06:26.081 --> 06:28.605
You were saying that he...

06:28.649 --> 06:30.607
- He said if I didn't...

06:31.782 --> 06:34.132
You know...

06:34.176 --> 06:36.874
he would go upstairs

06:36.918 --> 06:40.574
to my little sister Gizelle.
[crying]

06:43.098 --> 06:46.667
- So the rapist knew Lupe;
they knew her family.

06:46.710 --> 06:48.625
- It's why he didn't
let her get a look at him.

06:48.669 --> 06:52.586
- [sniffs]
He pulled down my pants...

06:52.629 --> 06:55.676
Please, I don't want
anyone to know that.

06:55.719 --> 06:59.549
- Hey...you don't have
to worry about that.

06:59.593 --> 07:01.595
- [sniffles]
- Okay?

07:02.944 --> 07:05.033
[knocking]

07:05.076 --> 07:07.818
- Lupe's mom is here.

07:11.779 --> 07:13.520
- I was working, um...

07:13.563 --> 07:15.217
My husband died two years ago,
that 9/11 cancer,

07:15.260 --> 07:16.871
so I work extra...

07:16.914 --> 07:18.742
[sniffles]
if I had been there...

07:18.786 --> 07:20.265
- You were working
for your family.

07:20.309 --> 07:23.138
Listen to me,
this is not your fault.

07:24.052 --> 07:28.099
- Ms. Perez, we think whoever
did this to Lupe knew her.

07:28.143 --> 07:30.275
So can you think of anyone,

07:30.319 --> 07:33.757
a neighbor, a teacher that
maybe pays too much attention?

07:33.801 --> 07:36.151
- No...um...
Lupe's always in the library

07:36.194 --> 07:38.501
or at the school lab or...

07:38.545 --> 07:42.462
babysitting her little sister.
[whimpering]

07:43.245 --> 07:46.640
[sniffles]
Please, I need to see Lupe.

07:47.597 --> 07:49.164
- Of course.

07:49.207 --> 07:50.731
- Last one.

07:50.774 --> 07:51.949
I cleared all
the registered sex offenders

07:51.993 --> 07:53.560
near Lupe's projects.

07:53.603 --> 07:57.085
- And no leads on the canvass.
Do we have anything?

07:57.128 --> 07:59.566
- Lupe said the perp's
hands were calloused,

07:59.609 --> 08:02.569
smelled like wood shavings.
Maybe a projects worker?

08:02.612 --> 08:04.832
- Okay, give me a list
of the maintenance guys

08:04.875 --> 08:06.834
from the Jacob Lawrence Houses.

08:06.877 --> 08:09.576
- I just got a weird hit
on the touch DNA

08:09.619 --> 08:11.142
from Lupe's headphones.

08:11.186 --> 08:14.624
It matches a double homicide
in the Wave View projects

08:14.668 --> 08:16.626
in Far Rockaway...

08:16.670 --> 08:19.194
from 2003.

08:21.196 --> 08:23.198
- You have a closed rape
and double murder

08:23.241 --> 08:24.808
from 16 years ago?

08:24.852 --> 08:26.244
And they had the DNA
and never tested it?

08:26.288 --> 08:27.942
- It was tested by mistake,

08:27.985 --> 08:29.639
swept up while they were
going through the backlog.

08:29.683 --> 08:31.902
- And the touch DNA on Lupe's
headphones matched the DNA

08:31.946 --> 08:34.165
found under the fingernails
of which victim?

08:34.209 --> 08:36.037
- Both.
Nydia Hernandez,

08:36.080 --> 08:38.343
strangled with an electric cord
and her daughter, Jacinta.

08:38.387 --> 08:40.171
She was sexually assaulted
and then strangled.

08:40.215 --> 08:41.912
- Two teenagers confessed.

08:41.956 --> 08:43.871
Ricardo Torres,
15 at the time.

08:43.914 --> 08:46.264
He turned state's
on Carlos Hernandez, 18,

08:46.308 --> 08:48.223
the son and brother
of the vics.

08:48.266 --> 08:49.833
- And which of their DNA
matches Lupe's?

08:49.877 --> 08:51.661
- That's the thing.
Neither.

08:51.705 --> 08:53.141
- What does that mean?

08:53.184 --> 08:55.143
That we're looking
at a third accomplice?

08:55.186 --> 08:57.058
- Someone who was never caught.

08:57.928 --> 09:00.017
- Okay, so we're gonna
need to talk with

09:00.061 --> 09:02.672
Ricardo and Carlos.
Where are they now?

09:02.716 --> 09:05.370
- Hernandez is still serving
25 to life in Green Haven.

09:05.414 --> 09:08.025
- 25 to life and he never
gave up the third guy?

09:08.069 --> 09:09.244
He's not talking.

09:09.287 --> 09:11.159
- So take Carisi with you.

09:11.202 --> 09:14.641
If he sees a DA, maybe he'll
think that he can cut a deal.

09:14.684 --> 09:16.904
And what about Ricardo?

09:16.947 --> 09:18.601
- Finished his 15 a year ago.

09:18.645 --> 09:20.603
Last known,
Wave View Houses in Far Rock.

09:20.647 --> 09:22.039
Parole officer's on vacay.

09:22.083 --> 09:23.388
- That's leverage.

09:23.432 --> 09:27.697
So, Rollins, Kat,
lean on him, hard.

09:27.741 --> 09:30.091
- Just to be clear,
we've got a guy doing life

09:30.134 --> 09:32.049
for murdering his mother
and his sister

09:32.093 --> 09:34.225
and there was someone else's
DNA on the victim?

09:34.269 --> 09:36.314
- Why check DNA?
They had confessions.

09:36.358 --> 09:37.794
- Yeah, and it's the projects.

09:37.838 --> 09:39.796
They were murdered
at a bad address.

09:45.672 --> 09:47.021
- I'm gonna ask you again,
Carlos,

09:47.064 --> 09:49.284
'cause we know
there was a third person

09:49.327 --> 09:51.852
who helped kill
your mama and your kid sis.

09:51.895 --> 09:53.288
- What you mean you know?

09:54.724 --> 09:57.901
- We found DNA of a third man.
- You did?

09:57.945 --> 09:59.990
So you know--
you know who did it.

10:00.034 --> 10:01.731
You arrest him?

10:01.775 --> 10:03.907
- If we knew who did it,
we wouldn't be asking.

10:03.951 --> 10:05.909
- Man, I don't know
who killed them.

10:05.953 --> 10:09.217
All I know is that Ricky
and me didn't do it, I swear.

10:09.260 --> 10:12.655
I could never hurt
my mommy or little Jacinta.

10:12.699 --> 10:15.092
That night, Ricky and me,
we was just hanging.

10:15.136 --> 10:17.181
- Really?
That's not what he said.

10:17.225 --> 10:19.401
This is
his handwritten confession.

10:19.444 --> 10:21.055
Says that the whole thing

10:21.098 --> 10:22.665
was your idea
and he just went along.

10:22.709 --> 10:24.406
- Ricky was just a kid.

10:24.449 --> 10:27.148
Detective Monte convinced him
if he turned state's on me,

10:27.191 --> 10:29.106
he'd get man two
and out in 15.

10:29.150 --> 10:30.934
- Then why'd you fess up?

10:30.978 --> 10:33.458
- Because Monte and the DA
told me if I didn't confess,

10:33.502 --> 10:36.157
that I'd get
the sayonara syringe.

10:36.200 --> 10:38.942
Man, I was 18.

10:38.986 --> 10:41.249
I didn't have no mommy
no more to help me.

10:41.292 --> 10:43.817
- Look, Carlos, I don't know
what went down then,

10:43.860 --> 10:45.775
but if you work with us now,

10:45.819 --> 10:47.298
you give up your accomplice,

10:47.342 --> 10:49.126
when you come up for parole,
I will go to the board.

10:49.170 --> 10:51.172
- Why do you keep
saying accomplice, man?

10:51.215 --> 10:52.913
I told you I wasn't even there.

10:52.956 --> 10:55.785
- Come on, man, everybody
in here says they're innocent.

10:55.829 --> 10:59.093
It's been 16 years.
That's almost half your life.

10:59.136 --> 11:00.877
Why are you
covering for this guy?

11:00.921 --> 11:02.749
- I swear to God,

11:02.792 --> 11:06.970
I came home and I saw them
lying there like that.

11:09.016 --> 11:10.974
It's all I've ever
thought about since.

11:11.018 --> 11:13.150
- Carisi,
this is a waste of time.

11:13.194 --> 11:14.804
- Hold on.

11:14.848 --> 11:16.414
Carlos, you said that--

11:16.458 --> 11:19.156
that you and Ricky were,
uh, you were hanging.

11:19.200 --> 11:21.202
Where?

11:24.771 --> 11:26.033
- That I can't say.

11:26.076 --> 11:27.469
- I told you this
was a waste of time.

11:27.512 --> 11:30.211
- Look, I'm not lying, okay?

11:31.516 --> 11:35.172
After he was released,
Ricky sent me this.

11:35.216 --> 11:37.174
He apologized for
putting me away.

11:37.218 --> 11:40.830
He said he was just saving
himself and back then...

11:40.874 --> 11:43.746
In Far Rock, we weren't angels.

11:43.790 --> 11:46.836
All right, but my mommy?
She was all I had.

11:46.880 --> 11:49.360
- Okay, you got
an alibi for that night?

11:49.404 --> 11:51.188
Or this goes nowhere.

11:55.410 --> 11:58.065
- Thank you for
your visit, gentlemen.

12:11.600 --> 12:11.774
.

12:11.818 --> 12:13.733
- Miss Baker?

12:14.951 --> 12:17.867
- Morning, detectives.
Help y'all?

12:17.911 --> 12:20.391
- Yes, ma'am.
You are Savannah Baker?

12:20.435 --> 12:24.787
- Well, the kids call me
"Moms," Moms Baker.

12:24.831 --> 12:26.833
Don't tell me another child

12:26.876 --> 12:28.399
has died
from them dopey-oids.

12:28.443 --> 12:29.792
- No, ma'am.

12:29.836 --> 12:31.272
We're here looking
for Ricardo Torrez.

12:31.315 --> 12:32.621
- The captain
of the housing unit

12:32.664 --> 12:33.709
thought you might
know where he is.

12:33.753 --> 12:35.406
- He paid his debt.

12:35.450 --> 12:36.973
- No, no, we just want
to ask a few questions.

12:37.017 --> 12:38.583
- And Carlos.

12:38.627 --> 12:40.672
No way he would
hurt a June bug,

12:40.716 --> 12:42.457
let alone his family.

12:42.500 --> 12:44.024
- You know about the murders.

12:44.067 --> 12:45.721
- I know he was a mama's boy.

12:45.765 --> 12:47.941
Never raised a hand
to hurt another child.

12:47.984 --> 12:49.681
- And what about Ricardo?

12:49.725 --> 12:53.337
- If Ricky threw himself
on the floor, he'd've missed.

12:53.381 --> 12:54.817
- But they both confessed.

12:54.861 --> 12:57.559
- Down home
we call that "railroading,"

12:57.602 --> 12:59.343
right, honey?

13:00.867 --> 13:02.694
[scoffs]

13:02.738 --> 13:04.827
Detective Monte...

13:04.871 --> 13:08.352
that prosecutor...

13:08.396 --> 13:11.747
They had the wrong boys,
but they didn't care.

13:11.791 --> 13:13.793
- Well, that's why we
want to talk to Ricardo.

13:13.836 --> 13:16.796
- Ricky lit right
back here from prison.

13:18.406 --> 13:21.975
He was so skinny.
I knew he had the bug.

13:22.018 --> 13:23.890
- HIV?

13:23.933 --> 13:28.329
- Full-blown AIDS.
He caught that while inside.

13:28.372 --> 13:30.070
He cried on my shoulder.

13:30.113 --> 13:33.377
He had lied on Carlos

13:33.421 --> 13:35.684
to save his own skin.

13:35.727 --> 13:38.295
- Moms, you know where
we can find Ricky?

13:38.339 --> 13:40.341
- He just passed.

13:40.384 --> 13:41.864
Last week.

13:41.908 --> 13:44.911
He asked me to, uh,

13:44.954 --> 13:47.435
scatter him out there

13:47.478 --> 13:51.874
where he and Carlos
skipped stones.

13:51.918 --> 13:53.658
- I'm so sorry.

13:55.835 --> 13:57.837
- Do you know who killed Ricky?

13:59.534 --> 14:02.537
That detective.

14:02.580 --> 14:05.801
You're sorry?
Talk to him.

14:12.112 --> 14:14.418
- You're retiring to Florida?

14:14.462 --> 14:16.072
Pension will go a lot further
down there, that's for sure.

14:16.116 --> 14:18.640
- Yeah, disability.
I'm out on three quarters.

14:18.683 --> 14:22.078
After collaring skells
like Hernandez and Torres,

14:22.122 --> 14:24.341
I don't wanna die
shoveling snow here

14:24.385 --> 14:25.908
in the stepchild borough.

14:25.952 --> 14:28.780
- I hear that.
- Carisi, huh?

14:28.824 --> 14:31.827
You related to Tony "No Toes"
Carisi up on Todt Hill?

14:31.871 --> 14:34.656
- My mother says
all Carisis are related.

14:34.699 --> 14:36.876
But about
Hernandez and Torres...

14:36.919 --> 14:38.616
you wrapped that
case up pretty quick.

14:38.660 --> 14:40.488
- First 48.
Listen, Counselor,

14:40.531 --> 14:42.925
you're not on the job.
Any cop who saw that scene,

14:42.969 --> 14:46.059
knew right away it had
to be banjos or bongos.

14:46.102 --> 14:49.062
The vics were PRs,
the mother was a crack putan,

14:49.105 --> 14:52.587
and the daughter was 13,
built like she was 23.

14:52.630 --> 14:54.850
Her son, Carlos, yeah,

14:54.894 --> 14:57.113
he was a big dopey stroonz,
horny as a bag of cats.

14:57.157 --> 14:58.854
- For his own sister, really?

14:58.898 --> 15:00.943
- An hour under the lamp
and the other one, Torres,

15:00.987 --> 15:02.902
flipped like an acrobat.

15:02.945 --> 15:05.165
A double homicide
cleared off the radio.

15:05.208 --> 15:06.862
Why do you two care?

15:06.906 --> 15:08.559
- We're working
a rape case, a young girl,

15:08.603 --> 15:09.821
and we got
a DNA hit that matches

15:09.865 --> 15:11.432
DNA from your crime scene.

15:11.475 --> 15:13.521
- It's gotta be Hernandez.
He was the doer.

15:13.564 --> 15:15.697
- No, neither.
Must've been a third man there.

15:15.740 --> 15:17.177
Do you remember
any other suspects?

15:17.220 --> 15:19.179
- Not a chance.
And let me tell you something.

15:19.222 --> 15:22.008
Those two--
it's not their first time.

15:22.051 --> 15:23.923
They were hitting
other projects.

15:23.966 --> 15:25.707
Three or four rapes,
teenage girls.

15:25.750 --> 15:28.449
Cases we couldn't make.
I just thank God

15:28.492 --> 15:31.104
that they were stupid enough
to hit their own home.

15:33.802 --> 15:35.499
- Carisi sent us cannolis

15:35.543 --> 15:37.023
from his favorite bakery
in Staten Island.

15:37.066 --> 15:38.981
- I'll make an exception.

15:39.025 --> 15:40.809
- So, aside from
the baked goods,

15:40.852 --> 15:42.071
did we get anything out there?

15:42.115 --> 15:43.638
- Pretty much
what we suspected.

15:43.681 --> 15:45.161
Detective Monte
wasn't interested in any

15:45.205 --> 15:46.684
other suspects
and Carisi thinks

15:46.728 --> 15:47.990
both confessions were coerced.

15:48.034 --> 15:49.600
- So we're not looking
for the third guy in,

15:49.644 --> 15:50.993
we're looking for the only guy.

15:51.037 --> 15:52.821
- The one that
got away with it.

15:52.864 --> 15:54.431
- You know, I thought
he was just trying to justify

15:54.475 --> 15:56.956
what he did,
but Monte--Monte did say

15:56.999 --> 15:58.522
that there'd been other rapes

15:58.566 --> 15:59.741
in the projects
around the same time.

15:59.784 --> 16:01.743
- So we could be
looking at a serial

16:01.786 --> 16:04.006
who's been out
there for 16 years.

16:05.268 --> 16:09.185
Okay, let's go back to unsolved
project rapes, check M.O.'s.

16:09.229 --> 16:10.752
Kat, you got the records

16:10.795 --> 16:12.884
of maintenance workers
at Lupe's projects, right?

16:12.928 --> 16:14.625
- Yep.

16:14.669 --> 16:16.627
- So cross check them and see
if anybody who worked there

16:16.671 --> 16:19.021
also worked at
Wave View 16 years ago.

16:22.546 --> 16:24.592
So we found 12
housing project rapes,

16:24.635 --> 16:26.768
but these two most
closely fit the pattern.

16:26.811 --> 16:29.945
- Maria Negron, 13.
Angela Lopez, 12.

16:29.989 --> 16:31.773
Both lived at
the Jersey Street projects.

16:31.816 --> 16:33.905
One happened in 2010,
the other in 2011.

16:33.949 --> 16:35.603
- No DNA on either?

16:35.646 --> 16:37.126
- No, they were both
assaulted from behind,

16:37.170 --> 16:38.736
strangled with a cord,

16:38.780 --> 16:40.477
and neither one of them
saw his face.

16:40.521 --> 16:41.826
- And that's his M.O.
Any suspects?

16:41.870 --> 16:44.090
- So there was 18
maintenance workers

16:44.133 --> 16:46.962
that worked at all
three of these projects

16:47.006 --> 16:48.659
that fit the timeline.

16:48.703 --> 16:51.227
Seven are black, two are
deceased, one is disabled.

16:51.271 --> 16:53.621
- So we're gonna need DNA
warrants on these eight guys.

16:53.664 --> 16:55.666
- Eight? Why not make it nine?
Make it a ball team.

16:55.710 --> 16:57.146
Come on, no judge
is gonna sign off on this.

16:57.190 --> 16:58.974
You gotta
narrow it down for me.

16:59.018 --> 17:01.194
- All right, so we can ask them
to volunteer for exclusion.

17:01.237 --> 17:02.804
If they're innocent,

17:02.847 --> 17:04.284
then they shouldn't
have a problem with that.

17:04.327 --> 17:05.981
- Okay, anybody balks,
I'll get you a warrant.

17:06.025 --> 17:07.765
- You're leaving us again?
- Got a pretrial motion.

17:07.809 --> 17:09.811
Feel free to stay
as long as you want.

17:09.854 --> 17:13.162
- All right,
so coordinate with Fin and Kat

17:13.206 --> 17:14.816
and make sure that
you talk to all eight guys.

17:14.859 --> 17:16.078
- Copy that.

17:16.122 --> 17:17.253
- I'll meet you
back in the squadroom.

17:17.297 --> 17:18.820
I have a lunch...

17:18.863 --> 17:20.213
with my brother, Simon.

17:20.256 --> 17:22.737
- Wow, it's been a while.
What does he want?

17:22.780 --> 17:25.870
- He says that he wants
to get to know Noah.

17:25.914 --> 17:27.916
- You believe him?

17:27.959 --> 17:30.049
- I do.

17:38.840 --> 17:41.799
- Tim Stanton.
[power drill buzzes]

17:41.843 --> 17:44.106
- Yeah?
- NYPD.

17:44.150 --> 17:45.890
Can we talk to you
for a minute?

17:45.934 --> 17:47.849
- Uh, they keep me pretty busy.

17:47.892 --> 17:49.285
- Yeah, well, we're here
investigating the assault

17:49.329 --> 17:50.939
from the other night.
You heard about that?

17:50.982 --> 17:52.201
- Yeah, horrible.

17:52.245 --> 17:53.681
- You're the maintenance guy.

17:53.724 --> 17:55.552
You been working
here for a long time?

17:55.596 --> 17:57.032
- They send me
where they need me.

17:57.076 --> 17:59.165
- Okay, well, you noticed
anybody that doesn't belong?

17:59.208 --> 18:00.905
Trying doors,
checking out the stairwell?

18:00.949 --> 18:03.256
- All the time.
Bangers, homeless, dealers.

18:03.299 --> 18:06.128
Got guys on the registry
in this neighborhood.

18:06.172 --> 18:08.043
- We're all over that.

18:08.087 --> 18:10.698
Just hoping maybe you could
come check out some mug shots.

18:10.741 --> 18:11.960
- Shouldn't the girl do that?

18:12.003 --> 18:13.353
- She didn't get
a good look at him.

18:13.396 --> 18:15.006
- Ah, that's too bad.

18:15.050 --> 18:16.834
Listen,
I'd do anything to help, but,

18:16.878 --> 18:18.184
I don't have a head for faces.

18:18.227 --> 18:20.055
- There's something
else you could do.

18:20.099 --> 18:22.971
We need your DNA to exclude
you from the investigation.

18:23.014 --> 18:26.148
- My DNA put in the system?
That ain't happening.

18:26.192 --> 18:29.020
Who knows what the government
does with that?

18:29.064 --> 18:31.197
- We're just asking you
for a little help.

18:31.240 --> 18:33.155
- Look, I feel
sorry for the girl,

18:33.199 --> 18:36.158
but I got places to be.

18:36.202 --> 18:38.073
You need anything else from me,

18:38.117 --> 18:40.597
let me know.

18:43.122 --> 18:45.211
- First guy to say no.

18:45.254 --> 18:47.256
I'm calling Carisi
for a warrant.

18:47.300 --> 18:49.824
- Yeah, save him the trouble.

18:49.867 --> 18:51.608
- In that case, I'll call Liv.

18:53.219 --> 18:56.004
- Great, and the lab knows
that it's a rush?

18:56.047 --> 18:57.745
Okay.

18:57.788 --> 19:00.313
Thanks, Rollins.
Nice work.

19:01.749 --> 19:03.229
- [groans]
When's your friend

19:03.272 --> 19:04.795
going to get here?

19:04.839 --> 19:06.145
- I don't know, honey.

19:06.188 --> 19:08.190
- I don't wanna be late
for dance class.

19:08.234 --> 19:09.974
- Okay, sweetie, I'm sorry.
I know.

19:10.018 --> 19:12.020
I'll find out.
I'll find out.

19:12.063 --> 19:13.978
Hi, excuse me.

19:14.022 --> 19:16.111
- Oh, did you want
to go ahead and order?

19:16.155 --> 19:18.200
- Actually, we're still
waiting for our third.

19:18.244 --> 19:20.637
Um, you're sure that
you didn't see a man,

19:20.681 --> 19:22.291
he had dark hair, light eyes...

19:22.335 --> 19:24.119
The reservation
was under Benson?

19:24.163 --> 19:26.165
- I'll check again.
- Thank you.

19:31.909 --> 19:34.303
You know what, Noah,
give me a second.

19:38.438 --> 19:41.876
Simon, it's me and Noah,

19:41.919 --> 19:44.226
and we are here
waiting for you.

19:44.270 --> 19:48.883
Listen, uh, I knew that
this was a bad idea,

19:48.926 --> 19:51.755
so...uh, don't--

19:51.799 --> 19:53.888
don't bother
calling me back, okay?

19:53.931 --> 19:58.022
As a matter of fact, Simon,
don't--don't ever call me.

20:06.901 --> 20:07.293
.

20:07.336 --> 20:09.338
- Captain.
- Good morning.

20:09.382 --> 20:11.514
- We got a match
on Tim Stanton.

20:11.558 --> 20:14.387
The lab confirms that
his DNA matches the touch DNA

20:14.430 --> 20:16.258
on Lupe's headphones
and the DNA found

20:16.302 --> 20:17.781
under the nails
of Jacinta and Nydia.

20:17.825 --> 20:19.653
- I was ready to arrest
that guy right there.

20:19.696 --> 20:23.178
- Hold on, let's wait.
Touch DNA on headphones...

20:23.222 --> 20:26.312
I'd like to see Lupe
make a positive ID...

20:26.355 --> 20:27.922
Where did you
leave it with Stanton?

20:27.965 --> 20:29.532
- He pretended like
he wanted to help.

20:29.576 --> 20:31.839
- So tell him that
we've collared a sex offender

20:31.882 --> 20:33.449
that we know is good for this

20:33.493 --> 20:34.929
and we just need help
with the lineup.

20:34.972 --> 20:36.626
- You think he'll go for that?

20:36.670 --> 20:38.411
- I think that he
let Hernandez and Torres

20:38.454 --> 20:40.195
take the fall before.

20:40.239 --> 20:41.936
He's just gonna think
that we've screwed up again.

20:41.979 --> 20:43.720
See if Lupe
is up for a lineup.

20:43.764 --> 20:45.766
- Cool.

20:49.552 --> 20:51.554
- So Lupe said
she didn't see him,

20:51.598 --> 20:53.382
but she did hear his voice.

20:53.426 --> 20:56.298
So if she can't do a lineup,
see if she can do a voice ID.

20:56.342 --> 20:58.779
- Yeah, copy that.
Um...listen,

20:58.822 --> 21:01.608
I was out of line--
what I said about your brother.

21:03.349 --> 21:05.307
- No, you weren't.

21:05.351 --> 21:07.309
Noah doesn't need any more
confusion about his life.

21:07.353 --> 21:11.357
That door's...
that door stays closed.

21:17.667 --> 21:19.713
- Take your time.

21:26.546 --> 21:28.896
- I didn't really see his face.

21:28.939 --> 21:30.985
- But you heard
his voice, right?

21:31.028 --> 21:33.335
- Yes.

21:33.379 --> 21:34.684
- Would you be okay hearing

21:34.728 --> 21:36.556
something that
he said to you again?

21:36.599 --> 21:39.428
- Mm-hmm.

21:40.951 --> 21:43.780
- Okay, number one.

21:43.824 --> 21:46.957
- Okay, chiquita,
do it nice for Papi.

21:48.350 --> 21:49.569
- Number two.

21:49.612 --> 21:51.484
- I'm not comfortable
saying this.

21:52.311 --> 21:53.660
- It's him.
- Just read the words.

21:53.703 --> 21:54.878
- Do I have to say this?

21:54.922 --> 21:56.402
- It's him.

21:56.445 --> 21:58.055
- Okay, chiquita,
do it nice for Papi.

21:58.099 --> 21:59.709
- It's him,
it's him, it's him.

21:59.753 --> 22:02.016
[sobbing]
It's him.

22:02.059 --> 22:04.366
It's him.
- It's okay.

22:04.410 --> 22:06.455
- [sobbing]
- It's okay.

22:06.499 --> 22:08.544
- Yeah, well, see,
I did some work

22:08.588 --> 22:10.546
on Lupe's mom's
bathroom recently,

22:10.590 --> 22:12.418
so I moved the kid's
headphones out of the way.

22:12.461 --> 22:14.376
I didn't--didn't want
to get no water on 'em.

22:14.420 --> 22:15.943
- That makes sense.

22:15.986 --> 22:18.728
- So I'm good to go?
- More like good to go away.

22:18.772 --> 22:20.382
We got another hit on your DNA,

22:20.426 --> 22:22.993
from a 16-year-old attack
in Far Rock.

22:23.037 --> 22:24.821
- The double murder?

22:24.865 --> 22:27.084
No, the son
and his buddy confessed.

22:27.128 --> 22:28.782
It can't be me.

22:28.825 --> 22:31.393
That's, uh, like,
double jeopardy or something.

22:31.437 --> 22:32.612
- Not really.

22:32.655 --> 22:36.093
- Besides,
even if my DNA was there...

22:36.137 --> 22:38.008
I probably worked
on that apartment, too.

22:38.052 --> 22:40.402
- Work?
That's how your blood and skin

22:40.446 --> 22:42.622
got under
the victim's fingernails?

22:44.450 --> 22:46.321
- All due respect,

22:46.365 --> 22:49.063
I think it's time for me
to shut down and lawyer up.

22:50.456 --> 22:51.979
- Well, he's right.

22:52.022 --> 22:53.981
It's gonna be pretty
hard to pin a double murder

22:54.024 --> 22:56.592
on him when there's somebody
still sitting in prison for it.

22:56.636 --> 22:59.116
- Lupe made a voice ID?
- She did.

22:59.160 --> 23:00.596
- All right, arrest Stanton,
keep him in holding.

23:00.640 --> 23:02.424
I'm gonna go up
and see Carlos Hernandez.

23:02.468 --> 23:04.731
See if he can ID this scumbag.

23:09.779 --> 23:12.478
- You just swipe.

23:14.567 --> 23:16.090
- What I remember
is those maintenance guys

23:16.133 --> 23:18.353
hardly ever came around.

23:20.486 --> 23:23.445
Him, we waited
over a year for him

23:23.489 --> 23:24.925
to fix Mommy's kitchen cabinet.

23:24.968 --> 23:26.143
- He was in your apartment,
you're sure?

23:26.187 --> 23:27.841
- Positive.

23:27.884 --> 23:29.495
There was a family of mice
living under the sink

23:29.538 --> 23:32.628
and I was scared to open it.

23:32.672 --> 23:34.500
Now I live with rats.

23:34.543 --> 23:37.154
This guy came,

23:37.198 --> 23:39.592
plugs mice holes,
fixes the cabinet.

23:42.029 --> 23:44.466
He even asked
Jacinta to teach him

23:44.510 --> 23:46.599
her Shakira dance moves.

23:48.078 --> 23:50.385
You think he killed them?

23:50.429 --> 23:52.474
- Well, there's no sign
of forced entry.

23:52.518 --> 23:54.476
Do you think your sister
would have let him in?

23:54.520 --> 23:56.478
- Any time any of those guys
came around, you let them in.

23:56.522 --> 23:59.089
You might not see
someone again for six months.

24:00.700 --> 24:02.484
Why would he kill them?

24:02.528 --> 24:05.922
- He's raping your sister,
your mother comes home...

24:07.837 --> 24:09.970
- He'd've had to kill her.

24:10.013 --> 24:11.624
He confess?

24:11.667 --> 24:14.017
- No.

24:14.061 --> 24:17.804
- But with his DNA, right,
and if Ricky testifies...

24:20.459 --> 24:22.461
- Ricky won't be testifying.

24:25.768 --> 24:27.161
- When did he pass?

24:27.204 --> 24:28.815
- A few days ago.

24:28.858 --> 24:32.862
- He felt bad about what
he did to me and to himself.

24:34.516 --> 24:36.083
He's at peace now.

24:36.126 --> 24:37.606
- And we still
have his letter.

24:37.650 --> 24:39.521
Plus the new DNA.

24:39.565 --> 24:40.914
I'm confident
when the Queens DA...

24:40.957 --> 24:44.047
- Queens DA?
Is it still Keane?

24:44.091 --> 24:46.615
- 16 years,
like the mummy's hand.

24:46.659 --> 24:49.052
- Man, that guy--
he got himself elected

24:49.096 --> 24:51.533
Queens DA
off of putting me away.

24:51.577 --> 24:53.056
- Listen, Carlos,

24:53.100 --> 24:55.058
I'm not gonna
promise you anything.

24:55.102 --> 24:57.713
But I do know somebody
that works in that office.

24:57.757 --> 24:59.628
A high ranking ADA.

24:59.672 --> 25:01.848
I trust him.
He's a good guy.

25:01.891 --> 25:04.938
- Yeah?
Why's he working for Keane?

25:09.943 --> 25:12.598
- So you did it?
- Hi.

25:12.641 --> 25:14.556
- From detective to ADA.
How's it going?

25:14.600 --> 25:17.124
- Oh, I miss my gun
and the pay cut's no fun,

25:17.167 --> 25:19.082
but I still remember

25:19.126 --> 25:20.562
what you said
my first year at Fordham Law.

25:20.606 --> 25:22.085
- Yeah, what was that?

25:22.129 --> 25:23.783
- Better 100 guilty men go free

25:23.826 --> 25:25.567
than one innocent man
be condemned.

25:25.611 --> 25:27.177
- You know
I was quoting Voltaire.

25:27.221 --> 25:29.571
- Of course, but it was
the way--the way you said it.

25:29.615 --> 25:31.094
It was like you believed in it.

25:31.138 --> 25:32.748
That's why I
brought this to you.

25:32.792 --> 25:34.576
Did you get a chance
to go over the case file?

25:34.620 --> 25:36.926
- Carlos Hernandez
had a terrible lawyer.

25:36.970 --> 25:38.928
He and Ricky, they were kids.

25:38.972 --> 25:42.018
They had their whole lives
taken from them.

25:42.062 --> 25:43.672
- So you can help
Carlos get out?

25:43.716 --> 25:45.761
- Look, it's tough to get
any DA to overturn a case,

25:45.805 --> 25:48.111
let alone over here in Queens.
But a rape and double murder

25:48.155 --> 25:49.939
my boss built his career on?

25:49.983 --> 25:51.854
- There's no DNA.

25:51.898 --> 25:53.595
Manhattan SVU has matched
it to a guy who's good

25:53.639 --> 25:55.205
for a series
of housing projects rapes.

25:55.249 --> 25:56.946
- Did he confess to this?

25:56.990 --> 25:58.513
Why would he?

25:58.557 --> 26:00.123
He knows it's a closed case,
two confessions.

26:00.167 --> 26:02.604
- They both recanted.
Ricky in a dying declaration.

26:02.648 --> 26:03.997
- Yeah, I read that, too.

26:04.040 --> 26:05.999
- I know this was Keane's case,

26:06.042 --> 26:07.609
but once he hears
the preponderance

26:07.653 --> 26:09.219
of exculpatory evidence...

26:09.263 --> 26:12.919
- You haven't heard...
about Keane.

26:18.838 --> 26:21.667
- DA Keane is
ready for you now.

26:23.364 --> 26:26.715
- Mr. Keane,
this is Manhattan ADA Carisi.

26:26.759 --> 26:29.326
- Nice to meet you, sir.
- You, too, Mr. Keane.

26:29.370 --> 26:31.981
Sir, I don't know if you've had
a chance to look over the...

26:32.025 --> 26:33.635
- What case are you here about?

26:33.679 --> 26:35.245
- The double homicide

26:35.289 --> 26:37.813
of Nydia and Jacinta Hernandez
in Far Rockaway.

26:37.857 --> 26:39.685
- You know why it's
called Far Rockaway?

26:41.338 --> 26:43.602
- No, sir, actually, I don't.

26:43.645 --> 26:45.168
- Because it's way far out.

26:45.212 --> 26:48.563
- It was also the scene
of a brutal double murder.

26:48.607 --> 26:50.217
It was your case, Mr. Keane.

26:50.260 --> 26:51.958
- The victim's son confessed,

26:52.001 --> 26:53.786
but his lawyer knew that
there was DNA at the scene.

26:53.829 --> 26:55.265
He didn't ask
for it to be tested.

26:55.309 --> 26:57.659
- Lawyers...
do you know that Shea Stadium

26:57.703 --> 26:59.269
was named because of a lawyer?

26:59.313 --> 27:02.969
Yes, William Shea.
It's still Shea Stadium.

27:03.012 --> 27:04.797
- I did know that one, sir.

27:04.840 --> 27:07.669
Um, now I know you're
very busy, Mr. Keane, but...

27:07.713 --> 27:09.845
the reason I'm here
is about getting justice

27:09.889 --> 27:11.194
for Carlos Hernandez.

27:11.238 --> 27:14.371
- Hernandez,
what a good first baseman.

27:14.415 --> 27:17.026
You know the Mets
couldn't have won anything

27:17.070 --> 27:18.941
in '86 without him.

27:20.334 --> 27:22.641
- I believe
that was Keith, sir.

27:22.684 --> 27:24.294
- Hmm.

27:24.338 --> 27:26.688
- I have some paperwork here
I'd like you to consider

27:26.732 --> 27:28.211
signing, agreeing to vacate

27:28.255 --> 27:29.778
the conviction
of Carlos Hernandez...

27:29.822 --> 27:31.867
- Put it over there
on the table.

27:31.911 --> 27:34.217
I'm very, very busy.
I'll do my best.

27:34.261 --> 27:39.048
